This pie is awesome! Made it for the first time today with a mix of frozen and fresh blueberries and it turned out great. The topping is crunchy and the berries are not runny. Wonderful taste with just a hint of citrus from the lemon. Will make this again. I'm thinking of trying this recipe with a mix of raspberries and blueberries or just raspberries. I'll let you know how they turn out.

Rating: 3
I used Pillsbury refrigerated pie dough, which I often do, but if you do, DO NOT blind bake it as long as this says. The original 20 minutes with weights (I use glass vase fillers) would have been enough. My crust was too dark, and I had to rim it with foil to bake with the filling. The filling is the best part. It has perfect consistency. Next time I will halve the lemon and omit the cinnamon in the crumble. Otherwise, we loved it.

