Very easy and yummy.

Rating: 4
Excellent recipe for blueberries! I am not a big blueberry pie fan, but this was delicious! It's very easy to make, not too sweet, and the blueberries don't dominate the recipe too much. The crust is very good. The only problem I had was that the crust stuck to the dish - but I think that was because some of the filling overflowed around the crust. So I'm not sure how to solve that for the future, but it still beautiful and exceptionally tasty. I will make this again. I don't recommend changing anything about the recipe either.

Rating: 4
Excellent blueberry pie recipe; I made it exactly as written. Typically I am not a blueberry pie fan - I make it for others in my family who love it at this time of year during blueberry season. This was the first blueberry pie recipe that I really enjoyed eating! The filling is not gooey like so many blueberry pie recipes - the berries stay whole and do not become too jam-like. Since the recipe does not specify, I chose to use a deep dish pie plate and would recommend this size to others - the filling did not boil over in the oven and the fruit filled the dish. Next time I would wait at least 2 hours before serving to allow the juices in the filling to fully set. A great recipe!

