This is a fantastic recipe. I have never made a "pretty pie" because the top crust is so elusive; the crumble topping solves this problem. I used 2 lb of frozen blueberries and followed the recipe as written except for the addition of 1/4 tsp of cardomom to the filling. Great flavor. It was the best blueberry pie ever. This recipe is a keeper.

Rating: 4
Yum!!! This was the best pie I have ever made! From now on I think I will just use a crumble instead of pie crust on top of all my pies. It had a nice balance of sweet and salty. Delicious.

Rating: 4
Loved this recipe!! It was easy to use, and I've already made it twice! Both times, I followed the other reviewers' suggestions to only use half the sugar (white and brown) for the topping. That was a great call. The second time I made this, I put a little more sugar in with the berries (maybe 1/8 cup) and about a teaspoon of lemon zest. That was a great add! I had used 2 cups blackberries (fresh) and 4 cups blueberries (frozen) and the berry part was a little too tart the first time. The extra sugar and lemon gave it such a nice flavor! I will definitely make this again. Super easy and a big crowd-pleaser!

