Rating: 4
This was excellent. Like janetlebeau, I used the Cook's Illustrated Foolproof Pie Dough, but otherwise followed the recipe. The filling has great flavor and the bake time was spot-on in my oven. I found that the pie needed to sit for ~1 hour after baking before I could make a clean cut (certainly you could eat it before then, but the filling would be more runny). Gorgeous and delicious!

Rating: 0
I have made this pie twice. I used my own recipe for the piecrust, (Cook's Illustrated Foolproof Pie Dough). It is very important to chill the pie shell before you blind bake it as it will shrink if you don't. The filling is amazing and the crumble very tasty. Be sure to let the blueberries sit in the sugar and cornstarch mixture as instructed so that the berries begin to release their juices. A bit hit with everyone in my family.

